Have you wondered how kelp makes babies Check this outthe dark patches pictured are calledsori they are responsible for seeding the future generation of kelp bedsThe sori is filled with spores and when the time is rightkelp releases their sorisee the holes on the right that s where sori has been released The sori sink to the ocean floor where the spores go through a number of steps before making baby kelps that attach to the rocks and start to grow up up upEventuallythey reach the surface of the oceanWe are mindful of this while harvesting by leaving behind kelp with the most prolific sori potential and harvesting kelp that has already released most of their sori

It was Halloween and the Barnacle team decided to go out for one last kelp harvestThere were rumors of spooky happenings going on in the bays and islands nearbybut knowing there was salsa to make they went out for a lookThe water was still and the fog thickbut otherwise all was well as they boated out to the kelp bedsAs the harvest began some strange things started to commenceMax noticed a piece of kelp curled around his legHe tripped as he bent over the deck for another pieceLia grabbed his life jacket and pulled him back aboardThat was closeAs they filled up totesthe kelp started spilling out on the deckNext thing they knew the kelp started taking on a spirit of its ownNo one knows what happened out there but this photo is all that remains from the team s log bookBe careful out there

Each piece of bull kelp is selected for qualitypulled up out of the big blueand cut off it s holdfastWe keep it cold while we bring it back to the Barnacle kitchen from the cool coastal watersFast forward a few more steps and it s ready for you in the form of tasty kelp salsapicklesand seasoningsbarnaclefoods com
